-- TEXT-Colombia central bank statement on interest rate decision
-- 
-- Fri May 30, 2014 02:45PM EDT
-- None



BOGOTA, May 30 (Reuters) - Colombia's central bank raised the benchmark lending rate 25 basis points to 3.75 percent on Friday, an increase aimed at containing a recent rise in still-low inflation as economic growth gathers momentum.

